{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idab7e2dc9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9511"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9511"},"text":"§ 9511.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this chapter:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab7e2dca-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9511/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The terms “aircraft”, “citizen of the United States”, “civil aircraft”, “person”, and “public aircraft” have the meanings given those terms by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s40102/a"},"text":"section 40102(a) of title 49","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab7e2dcb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9511/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “passenger-cargo combined aircraft” means a civil aircraft equipped so that its main deck can be used to carry both passengers and property (including mail) simultaneously.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab7e2dcc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9511/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “cargo-capable aircraft” means a civil aircraft equipped so that all or substantially all of the aircraft’s capacity can be used for the carriage of property or mail.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab7e2dcd-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9511/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “passenger aircraft” means a civil aircraft equipped so that its main deck can be used for the carriage of individuals and cannot be used principally, without major modification, for the carriage of property or mail.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab7e2dce-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9511/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “cargo-convertible aircraft” means a passenger aircraft equipped or designed so that all or substantially all of the main deck of the aircraft can be readily converted for the carriage of property or mail.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab7e2dcf-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9511/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “Civil Reserve Air Fleet” means those aircraft allocated, or identified for allocation, to the Department of Defense under section 101 of the Defense Production Act of 1950 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s4511"},"text":"50 U.S.C. 4511","children":[],"tail":"), or made available (or agreed to be made available) for use by the Department of Defense under a contract made under this title, as part of the program developed by the Department of Defense through which the Department of Defense augments its airlift capability by use of civil aircraft."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab7e2dd0-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9511/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “contractor” means a citizen of the United States (A) who owns or controls, or who will own or control, a new or existing aircraft and who contracts with the Secretary under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s9513"},"text":"section 9513 of this title","children":[],"tail":" to modify that aircraft by including or incorporating specified defense features in that aircraft and to commit that aircraft to the Civil Reserve Air Fleet, (B) who subsequently obtains ownership or control of a civil aircraft covered by such a contract and assumes all existing obligations under that contract, or (C) who owns or controls, or will own or control, new or existing aircraft and who, by contract, commits some or all of such aircraft to the Civil Reserve Air Fleet."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab7e2dd1-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9511/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “existing aircraft” means a civil aircraft other than a new aircraft.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab7e2dd2-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9511/9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9"},"text":"(9)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “new aircraft” means a civil aircraft that a manufacturer has not begun to assemble before the aircraft is covered by a contract under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s9513"},"text":"section 9513 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab7e2dd3-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9511/10"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"10"},"text":"(10)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of Defense.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab7e2dd4-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9511/11"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"11"},"text":"(11)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “defense feature” means equipment or design features included or incorporated in a civil aircraft which ensures the compatibility of such aircraft with the Department of Defense airlift system. Such term includes any equipment or design feature which enables such aircraft to be readily modified for use as an aeromedical aircraft or a cargo-convertible, cargo-capable, or passenger-cargo combined aircraft.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idab7e2dd5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s9511/12"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"12"},"text":"(12)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “Civil Reserve Air Fleet program” means the program developed by the Department of Defense through which the Department of Defense augments its airlift capability by use of civil aircraft.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idab7e2dd6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/86/tIX/s915/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–86, title IX, § 915(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-12-01"},"text":"Dec. 1, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/1125"},"text":"95 Stat. 1125","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/180/dA/tXII/s1231/17"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–180, div. A, title XII, § 1231(17)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-12-04"},"text":"Dec. 4, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/1161"},"text":"101 Stat. 1161","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/456/dA/tXII/s1233/k/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–456, div. A, title XII, § 1233(k)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-09-29"},"text":"Sept. 29, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/2058"},"text":"102 Stat. 2058","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/189/dA/tXVI/s1636/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–189, div. A, title XVI, § 1636(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/1609"},"text":"103 Stat. 1609","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/272/s5/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–272, § 5(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-07-05"},"text":"July 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/1373"},"text":"108 Stat. 1373","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/tIII/s3031"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355, title III, § 3031","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/3334"},"text":"108 Stat. 3334","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/92/dA/tX/s1085/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–92, div. A, title X, § 1085(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2015-11-25"},"text":"Nov. 25, 2015","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/129/1005"},"text":"129 Stat. 1005","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/328/dA/tX/s1081/b/4/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–328, div. A, title X, § 1081(b)(4)(C)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/2419"},"text":"130 Stat. 2419","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/81/dA/tX/s1083/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–81, div. A, title X, § 1083(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (c)(1)(B), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-12-27"},"text":"Dec. 27, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/135/1922"},"text":"135 Stat. 1922","children":[],"tail":", 1923.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idab7e2dd7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idab7e2dd8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idab7e2dd9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—Pars. (7), (9). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/81/s1083/c/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–81, § 1083(c)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 9513” for “section 9512”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (10). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/81/s1083/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–81, § 1083(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", amended par. (10) generally. Prior to amendment, par. (10) read as follows: “The term ‘Secretary’ means the Secretary of the Air Force.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2016—Par. (6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/328"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–328","children":[],"tail":" substituted “("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s4511"},"text":"50 U.S.C. 4511","children":[],"tail":")” for “(50 U.S.C. App. 2071)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2015—Par. (12). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/92"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–92","children":[],"tail":" added par. (12)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/s3031/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355, § 3031(c)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “In this chapter:” for “In this subchapter:” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/s3031/b/1/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355, § 3031(b)(1)(C)","children":[],"tail":", which directed substitution of “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s40102"},"text":"section 40102 of title 49","children":[],"tail":"” for “section 101 of the Federal Aviation Act of 1958 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s1301"},"text":"49 U.S.C. 1301","children":[],"tail":")”, could not be executed because of the intervening amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/272"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–272","children":[],"tail":" which substituted “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s40102/a"},"text":"section 40102(a) of title 49","children":[],"tail":"” for “section 101 of the Federal Aviation Act of 1958 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s1301"},"text":"49 U.S.C. 1301","children":[],"tail":")”, see below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/s3031/b/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355, § 3031(b)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", (B), inserted “ ‘civil aircraft’,” before “ ‘person’,” and substituted “meanings” for “meaning”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/272"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–272","children":[],"tail":" substituted “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s40102/a"},"text":"section 40102(a) of title 49","children":[],"tail":"” for “section 101 of the Federal Aviation Act of 1958 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s1301"},"text":"49 U.S.C. 1301","children":[],"tail":")”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/s3031/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355, § 3031(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3), redesignated par. (7) as (6) and struck out former par. (6) which read as follows: “The term ‘civil aircraft’ means an aircraft other than a public aircraft.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/s3031/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355, § 3031(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated par. (8) as (7). Former par. (7) redesignated (6)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (8). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/s3031/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355, § 3031(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated par. (9) as (8). Former par. (8) redesignated (7)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/s3031/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355, § 3031(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s9512"},"text":"section 9512 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” after “and who contracts with the Secretary” in subpar. (A) and added subpar. (C)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Pars. (9), (10). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/s3031/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355, § 3031(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated pars. (10) and (11) as (9) and (10), respectively. Former par. (9) redesignated (8)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (11). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/s3031/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355, § 3031(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", (4), redesignated par. (12) as (11), substituted “compatibility” for “interoperability”, and inserted “an aeromedical aircraft or” before “a cargo-convertible”. Former par. (11) redesignated (10)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (12). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/s3031/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355, § 3031(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated par. (12) as (11)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—Par. (2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/189/s1636/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–189, § 1636(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", amended par. (2) generally. Prior to amendment, par. (2) read as follows: “The term ‘cargo air service’ means the carriage of property or mail on the main deck of a civil aircraft.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/189/s1636/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–189, § 1636(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", amended par. (5) generally. Prior to amendment, par. (5) read as follows: “The term ‘cargo-convertible feature’ means equipment or design features included or incorporated in a passenger aircraft that can readily enable all or substantially all of that aircraft’s main deck to be used for the carriage of property or mail.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (8)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/189/s1636/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–189, § 1636(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “a new or existing aircraft and who contracts with the Secretary to modify that aircraft by including or incorporating specified defense features” for “a civil aircraft and who contracts with the Secretary of the Air Force to modify that aircraft by including or incorporating cargo-convertible features suitable for defense purposes”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (12). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/189/s1636/a/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–189, § 1636(a)(4)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (12)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Par. (1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/456"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–456","children":[],"tail":" substituted “The terms” for “The term”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1987—Pars. (1) to (11). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/180"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–180","children":[],"tail":" inserted “The term” after each par. designation, and revised first word in quotes in pars. (1) to (6) and (8) to (10) to make initial letter of each word lowercase."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idab7e2dda-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idab7e2ddb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1994 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For effective date and applicability of amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/s10001"},"text":"section 10001 of Pub. L. 103–355","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s8752"},"text":"section 8752 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
